description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;St Ann&#39;s Hospice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At St Ann’s, there’s one thing that motivates us, and that’s providing excellent care and support to those living with or affected by life-limiting illnesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re continuously developing our plans for delivering world-class, innovative care and to ensure St Ann’s is in the best shape possible for future generations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be challenged, inspired and empowered to help us achieve our purpose and to play your part in making a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have you got what it takes?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you an experienced Occupational Therapist with skills supporting people with life limiting illnesses?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can you demonstrate leadership and management skills?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must be passionate about our patients and a collaborative colleague&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Most importantly, you must be wholeheartedly committed to and motivated by the purpose and values of St Ann’s Hospice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time permanent posistion. The working pattern is 37.5 hours per week 5/7 days. Working cross site at our Heald Green and Little Hulton site. This pay scale is set at St Ann&#39;s Hospice pay scale of Band 7 £38, 984-£44, 855.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join an ambitious, much loved charity and help us achieve our goals. If you’re looking for a new challenge and the opportunity to make a difference, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An Enhanced DBS check will be required, the cost of which is covered by the hospice. St Ann’s Hospice is committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of adults at risk and children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
